1. Partition Types

ðŸ”§ Example: View partition table

sudo fdisk -l

2. Filesystem Types

ðŸ”§ Example: Format a partition with XFS


sudo mkfs.xfs /dev/sdb1

3. Mounting

ðŸ”§ Example: Mount a USB drive


sudo mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt/usb
Unmount:


sudo umount /mnt/usb

 4. Automount

ðŸ”§ Example: Auto-mount with fstab


# Add to /etc/fstab
/dev/sdb1  /mnt/usb  xfs  defaults  0 0

# Test
sudo mount -a


 5. File Types

ðŸ”§ Example: Check file types


ls -l
Look at first character:


# Example output
-rw-r--r-- file.txt       # regular
drwxr-xr-x folder/        # directory
lrwxrwxrwx link -> file   # symlink

6. File Security

ðŸ”§ Example: Set file permissions


# Create and restrict access
touch secret.txt
chmod 600 secret.txt
chown student:student secret.txt
























